### Example 2: Manage Program Counter

#### ❌ BEFORE (SQL)

```vb
' Lines 253-261 in ExService.vb
Dim dt_counter As DataTable = BeConnM.GetDt("Select counter from Machines_Extractor_AOI_Programs where partid=@PartID and aoiid=@AOIID and side=@Side", GetCounterParameter)

If dt_counter.Rows.Count > 0 Then
    counter = dt_counter.Rows(0).Item(0) + 1
    BeConnM.UpdateRecords("UPDATE Machines_Extractor_AOI_Programs SET counter='" & counter & "'  where partid=@PartID and aoiid=@AOIID and side=@Side", GetCounterParameter)
Else
    counter = 1
    BeConnM.InsertRecords("INSERT INTO Machines_Extractor_AOI_Programs ([AOIID] ,[ProgramName] ,[ArrQty] ,[PartID] ,[Side] ,[Counter]) VALUES (@AOIID,'',@ArrQty,@PartID,@Side,'1')", GetCounterParameter)
End If
```

#### ✅ AFTER (API)

```vb
' Get program counter
Dim programCounter As AOIProgramCounter = AOI.GetProgramCounter(AOIID, partid, sideid)

If programCounter IsNot Nothing AndAlso programCounter.AutoId > 0 Then
    ' Program exists - increment counter
    counter = programCounter.Counter + 1
    AOI.UpdateProgramCounter(AOIID, partid, sideid, counter)
Else
    ' Program doesn't exist - create with counter = 1
    counter = 1
    AOI.CreateOrUpdateProgram(AOIID, partid, sideid, quantityUnitsScanned, counter)
End If
```

**Benefits:**
- ✅ Upsert logic handled by API
- ✅ No need to check if record exists
- ✅ Type-safe return values
- ✅ No string concatenation for SQL

